@node "whatisit" "What is it?"

  What is  it  ?

  In short  Smartie  has  three  purposes:

       - to help you handle XPK packing/unpacking of files via powerful GUI
       interface

       - to enable use of XPK-packed  files  in  programs  which  does  not
       support   XPK   standard  (text  editors,  painting  programs,  DTP,
       databeases etc.

       - make XPK-packed programs executable

  Unfortunately there is a lot of good programs  which  don't  support
  packing at all or are using different little known or very old (like
  powerpacker) methods. So this is where this program comes in  handy.
  It   patches   system  routines  @{i}Open,  Close,  Write,  LoadSeg,
  LoadNewSeg@{ui} to check if file  or  program  is  packed.  You  may
  specify  which  files  should be packed/unpacked upon calls of Open,
  Close via AmigaDos patterns. Moreover you may also  specify  calling
  task  (also  with  patterns).  That  makes it possible to exclude or
  include certain files or whole directories  (even  partitions)  from
  processing.

  When certain file to be processed is opened by calling task, Smartie
  will  check  if  it  is  compressed  or  not and if it is it will be
  decompressed. You may use password encryption. Requester will appear
  to ask you for password.

  Number of packing processes on one file is not limited. You may have
  file  which  is  packed  in  one  method and encrypted in other one.
  Smartie will try unpacking this file for as long as needed.

  When calling task tries to close file (by calling Close routine), it
  will be compressed. You may specify two packing methods in Smartie's
  preferences window: one for compression and one for  encryption.  It
  is  recommended  to  compress  file  first  (first  method) and then
  encrypt it (second method) because encrypting of large  uncompressed
  files is time consuming event.

@endnode
