@node "smartiestartup" "Smartie window's Startup menu"

  Options set in this menu will take effect only upon new start of the
  program.  Therefore  it is necessary to save settings before exiting
  program.

  @{" CX priority " link smartiecxpriority 0}
  @{" PREF popkey " link smartieprefpopkey 0}
  @{" FONT 1 " link smartiefont1 0}
  @{" Temporary path " link smartietemporarypath 0}
  @{" Data file " link smartiedatafile 0}
  @{" Pop up PREF window " link smartiepopupprefwindow 0}
  @{" Set language " link smartiesetlanguage 0}

@endnode
@node "smartieabout"

  About

  Guess what it does? Yeah, its information about Smartie program.

@endnode
@node "smartieuse"

  Use

  Closes PREF window. All set parameters are in effect.

@endnode
@node "smartiesave"

  Save

  Will save all entries to a file. See gadget explanation about how to
  make such entry.

@endnode
@node "smartiequit"

  Quit

  You won't believe it. This just quits the program.

@endnode
@node "smartiexpkfiles"

  XPK files

  When set Smartie will  patch  Open/Close/Write  routines  to  enable
  programs use XPK packed files.

@endnode
@node "smartiexpkexecutables"

  XPK executables

  Will turn on patch of LoadSeg/NewLoadSeg. When  checked  it  enables
  you to run XPK packed executables.

@endnode
@node "smartiesearch"

  Search

  Options to take effect when deciding which file should be processed.
  Path pattern  - will search only entered file paths with patterns
  Program pattern  - will search only entered program with patterns
  Both  - will search both file and program patterns

@endnode
@node "smartiecasesensitivity"

  Case sensitivity

  Turns on case sensitive search of entered programs.
  You may have case sensitive path or program or both.

@endnode
@node "smartiepassword"

  Password

  Options for  password  (when  using  encrypted  files)
  Invisible - password will not be visible. Be aware what you enter!
  Show last - when password requester appears again, last password
              will be shown.
  Repeat    - program asks you to confirm entered password

@endnode
@node "smartieclosegadget"

  Close gadget

  When checked, close gadget will exit the program, else it will  only
  hide Smartie window.

@endnode
@node "smartiequiet"

  Quiet

  When checked, Smartie will suppress all messages like errors etc.

@endnode
@node "smartieshowcallingprogram"

  Show calling program

  When checked, Smartie will show you the name of program (task) which
  is opening specified file. Useful when file should be processed only
  with certain task.

@endnode
@node "smartiesavesettings"

  Save settings

  Will save all  settings  into  icon's  tooltypes.  Also  options  and
  parameters for XPK window are saved with this action.

@endnode
@node "smartiecxpriority"

  CX priority

  Will set CX (commoditie's priority). Values are -127  (lowest)  upto
  +127  (highest).

  Options set in Startup menu will take effect only after  restart  of
  the  program.  Saving  of all options is needed (menu Settings, item
  Save settings).

@endnode
@node "smartieprefpopkey"

  PREF popkey

  Will set popkey for  PREF  window.  Any  valid  commoditie's  hotkey
  allowed.

  Options set in Startup menu will take effect only after  restart  of
  the  program.  Saving  of all options is needed (menu Settings, item
  Save settings).

@endnode
@node "smartiefont1"

  Font 1

  Will set font 1 used by Smartie window and partially by  XPK  window
  Program  was  designed to be used with XCourier.font 13. Other fonts
  and sizes may not fit in Smarties window.

  Options set in Startup menu will take effect only after  restart  of
  the  program.  Saving  of all options is needed (menu Settings, item
  Save settings).

@endnode
@node "smartietemporarypath"

  Temp path

  Will set temporary path where all unpacking and packing takes place.
  Usually  it  is t:, but if you are short of memory you may use other
  directory. This option works even without saving of settings.

@endnode

@endnode
@node "smartiedatafile"

  Data file

  Will set path of data file (should end with .data) which contains all entries
  of SMARTIE window. By default it is s:smartie.data.

  Options set in Startup menu will take effect only after  restart  of
  the  program.  Saving  of all options is needed (menu Settings, item
  Save settings).

@endnode

@node "smartiepopupprefwindow"

  Popup PREF window

  When checked, PREF window is opened upon startup of the  program  or
  when  opened by programs like Exchange. Opening by Exchange programs
  takes effect even without saving of settings.

  Options set in Startup menu will take effect only after  restart  of
  the  program.  Saving  of all options is needed (menu Settings, item
  Save settings).

@endnode
@node "smartiesetlanguage"

  Set language

  Will set locale's language (like english, german, czech etc.).  When
  no languge is set (gadget is cleared) default language will be used.

  Options set in Startup menu will take effect only after  restart  of
  the  program.  Saving  of all options is needed (menu Settings, item
  Save settings).

@endnode




